while true (fabric) by Lars Wander
collections.description:
Art Blocks Collection: Curated

Project Description: The while true (fabric) collection contains four jacquard fabric panels, crafted from an artist-selected hash code, produced to reflect the rich variety of while true. The fabric is paired with a digital artwork, selected by the artist, to correspond with it.

while true is a meditation on the meaning of unboundedness. Infinity is a strange and paradoxical concept: nothing real can be “infinite”, yet the math and physics we use to describe and understand our universe is built on the concept of its existence. Take away infinity and the groundwork that ties together calculus, probability theory, differential equations and countless more fields begins to crumble. Throughout history, many philosophers have raised issues in including infinity in our metaphysical and mathematical reasoning: Brouwer and his school of intuitionism strongly rejected the idea of using impossible concepts in mathematics, arguing that math should be constructible. Aristotle rejected the idea of “actual” infinity, seeing it as something impossible. Kronecker, who famously said “God made the integers, all else is the work of man”, objected to the use of infinity and transfinite numbers in math. There is clearly truth to the fact that any infinite object is too large or impossible for our minds to truly comprehend, but infinity has clearly shown its undeniable effectiveness in helping construct models of reality. All this leaves the question: how do we explain the infinite?

The collection emerges from an intentional coexistence  between algorithmic spontaneity and human intention—handpicked pigments to become data, shades translated into numerical poetry, and digital patterns gracefully morph into physical impressions on canvas. Each piece is a vivid negotiation, bridging the ethereal realm of code as scaffolding for the tangible texture of inks, inviting viewers to intimately reconnect with generative art through visual depth and the palpable craftsmanship of plotting, a skill I've meticulously honed over the past three years in my lab.

collections.name: Punk Ladies Collection
collections.description:
Considering myself an admirer of Crypto Punks, I often thought about an hypothetical future for their characters. In this case, more specifically I was thinking what the female characters would be like in the future. It was funny to imagine what they had become. The collection Punk Ladies illustrates this… literally.
   What could have happened with to them?
   Did they explored the seven continents? Were they in search of themselves through meditation? Did they become animal parties because show must go on? Did they decide to save whales, puppies and kittens? Did they move to another urban tribe before returning to their origins?
   Any experience that we can assume that punk ladies had will never cancel out that simple fact that within them the rebellious essence will always be present, because the Punk legacy will always live on!
